{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"actuarial-germfree-wasp","description":"## Why\n\nThree low-severity test-quality issues from the validation are worth cleaning up:\n\n- The post-deletion smoke test\n  (`tests/integration/rebar_reconciler/test_post_deletion_smoke.py`) invokes each leaf\n  but catches/ignores every exception except `ModuleNotFoundError` and asserts only that\n  the registry has `>=6` entries — it is linkage coverage but is named/positioned as if\n  it proves every leaf is invocable.\n- `test_repair_json_receives_schema` only asserts the schema object is forwarded as a\n  kwarg; it never shows schema guidance changes a parsed result.\n- `test_capture_baseline_not_implemented_error_not_raised` asserts only `is not None`,\n  duplicating stronger neighboring baseline tests.\n\n## What\n\n- Rename/rescope the smoke test to what it actually proves, add a behavioral\n  schema-guided parse test, and remove/fold the redundant baseline test.\n\n## Scope\n\n- `tests/integration/rebar_reconciler/test_post_deletion_smoke.py`\n- `tests/unit/test_silent_success.py`\n- `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/orchestrate/test_health_baseline.py`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] The post-deletion smoke test is renamed to reflect stale-import/linkage detection\n      and its docstring/coverage note scopes it to linkage only (prefer importing/\n      resolving referenced modules over pretend-executing every leaf).\n- [ ] A new test uses a real schema + a stable ambiguous payload where json-repair's\n      schema-guided result differs from schema-less; it asserts `tolerant_parse(schema=)`\n      and `parse_structured` return the expected object. The forwarding spy is kept only\n      as a narrow integration check.\n- [ ] `test_capture_baseline_not_implemented_error_not_raised` is deleted or folded into\n      the strongest baseline test.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass.","id":"2da6-918a-16ca-4b24","parent_id":"cc4d-7be4-dc0b-497f","priority":3,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Test-suite hygiene: post-deletion smoke, schema-guided parse, redundant baseline"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783886371694108001,"uuid":"e05f7c57-2105-47c9-a21a-865ee8f0a1ab"}